'''Kasuga Shrine''' (かすがじんじゃ) is a Shinto shrine located in {{jalink|Osaka Prefecture|Q122723}}, {{jalink|Ibaraki City|Q502403}}. It is an {{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932}}-listed {{jalink|Settsu Province|Q864163}} {{jalink|Shimashimo District|Q10976940}} {{jalink|Shikinaisha}} and is regarded as a {{jalink|ronsa|Q135022904}} (shrine identified through scholarly debate).

=== History ===
One of the two seats of the Shikinaisha {{jalink|Sukuku Shrine|Q11664487}}, according to the “Jingū Zōreishū,” on April 5 of {{jalink|Tenpyō era|Q1199879}} 12 ({{jalink|740|Q23593}}), {{jalink|Minister of the Right|Q1351174}} {{jalink|Ōnakatomi no Kiyomaro|Q11431854|Nakatomi no Kiyomaro}} secluded himself at this site and enshrined his ancestral deities near his residence.
* In {{jalink|Meireki era|Q1192766}} 1 ({{jalink|1655|Q6975}}), it became independent from the affiliated villages of Moto-Sukuku-shō Village and came to be called {{jalink|Kasuga Shrine|Q10855011}}.
* In {{jalink|Meiji era|Q3125096}} 5 ({{jalink|1872|Q7753}}), it was ranked as a {{jalink|village shrine|Q134917284}}.
* On August 28, {{jalink|Heisei era|Q234510}} 22 ({{jalink|2010|Q1995}}), a fire caused by suspected arson destroyed the main hall and worship hall.
* On March 25, Heisei 24 ({{jalink|2012|Q1990}}), reconstruction of the main hall and worship hall was completed.

=== Enshrined deities ===
[[File:Simizu 003.JPG|thumb|right|Former worship hall before the fire]]
* {{jalink|Amenokoyane-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Takemikazuchi|Q1502690|Takemikazuchi-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Futsunushi-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Himegami|Q22070227|Hime-Ōkami}}

=== References ===
* Yukihiko Tembō, “Historic Sites and Scenic Places of Mishima District” (1961) (included in *Historic Sites, Scenic Places, and Natural Monuments of Osaka Prefecture*, Mishima District (1974), edited by the Osaka Prefectural Department of Education) {{National Bibliography Number|73009804}}
* Ibaraki City Board of Education, “Our Town Ibaraki: Shrines and Temples Edition” (1989) {{National Bibliography Number|89049621}}

